place.name: WELBORNE
place.gazetteerText: WELBORNE, a parish in Forehoe district, Norfolk; 3¼ miles NNE of Hardingham r. station, and 6½ NNW of Wymondham. Post town, Dereham. Acres, 732. Real property, £1,633. Pop., 200. Houses, 41. The manor belongs to J. Cuddon, Esq.; and much of the land, to O. S. Olney, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £250.* Patron, the Rev. J. B. Johnson. The church was restored in 1852. There are a national school, and charities £9. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
